H3.text: Marjorie Courtenay-Latimer discovered which rare fish in 1938. Xelacanth

A4.text: Smith named the new coelacanth Latimeria chalumnae in honor of Marjorie Courtenay-Latimer and the waters in which it was found.

A5.text: When Smith returned, he immediately recognized it as a type of coelacanth, a group of fish previously known only from fossils.

A6.text: The first Latimeria specimen was found off the east coast of South Africa, off the Chalumna River (now Tyolomnqa).

A7.text: The genus name Latimeria commemorates Marjorie Courtenay-Latimer, who discovered the first specimen.
